Package astManager

Package for all the classes that are meant to deal with the Abstract Syntax Tree of the Source Code.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ASTHandler
    Class to hold all the AST for the application in a form that is convenient to evaluate software metrics on.
    BaseAST
    Base class for the wrapper classes holding the JavaParser AST
    Breadcrumb
    Class that contains the location of a particular node, in the form of the keys used to access it from the astStorage object in ASTHandler.
    ClassAST
    AST wrapper for AST needded to evaluate class level metrics
    MethodAST
    AST wrapper for ast needed to evaluate method level metrics
    PackageAST
    AST wrapper for AST needed to evaluate project level metrics
    ProjectAST
    AST wrapper for ast needed to evaluate project level metrics
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidOperationException
    For use with BaseAST - when one of the subclasses tries to call a method that is not supported for that subclass - like getParent for a ProjectAST.

Package astManager Description

Package for all the classes that are meant to deal with the Abstract Syntax Tree of the Source Code. Meant to keep the parsing modular, and enable different source languages eventually.
Author:
Jacob Botha
